3. cs.SP (Speech Processing): The techniques and results presented in the paper may have applications in speech processing, where bandwidth-limited channels with quantization are common. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper's focus on bandwidth-limited channels and quantization may be relevant to multimedia applications such as video and audio streaming.
